In design.md Section 4 (sync pipeline PERM# processing), change the update strategy to use scripted_upsert:

```json
{
  "scripted_upsert": true,
  "script": {
    "source": "if (ctx._source.sharedWithUserIds == null) { ctx._source.sharedWithUserIds = [params.userId] } else if (!ctx._source.sharedWithUserIds.contains(params.userId)) { ctx._source.sharedWithUserIds.add(params.userId) }",
    "params": { "userId": "user_xyz" }
  },
  "upsert": {
    "sharedWithUserIds": ["user_xyz"]
  }
}
```

Add a note: 'Using scripted_upsert ensures that if the PERM# event arrives before the METADATA event, a minimal document is created. When the METADATA event arrives later, the full document will be indexed and the sharedWithUserIds field will be preserved via the transform.'

Update tasks 1.5 and 1.7 to specify scripted_upsert behavior. Add test case in 1.9 for 'PERM# update when collection document does not yet exist in OpenSearch'.
